sh
# Interpreter for 'vpn-switch session clean' command
# Terminal function that generates shell commands to remove stale symlinks
#
# Default value: "sh"
#   Scans session/ directory for symlinks pointing to removed sessions
#   Removes any stale symlinks to keep session/ directory clean
#
# Bug #5 Fix: Manual cleanup command for stale session symlinks
#   Session symlinks can become stale when:
#   - Session directories are removed manually
#   - System crashes leave orphaned symlinks
#   - Concurrent stop operations race with symlink cleanup
#
# Session clean workflow:
#   1. Lists all symlinks in session/ directory
#   2. Checks if each symlink target exists
#   3. Removes symlinks pointing to non-existent sessions
#
# Example usage:
#   vpn-switch session clean     # Remove all stale symlinks
#
# Advanced - dry-run mode:
#   echo "cat" > .env/local/VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_session_clean
#   vpn-switch session clean     # Preview commands without executing
